<P>
<S ID='S-41' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> Clearly , the event described by the past perfect sentence must precede the event described by the first , simple past sentence . </S>
<S ID='S-42' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> However , if a third sentence is added , an ambiguity results . </S>
<S ID='S-43' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> Consider the following possible continuations of <CREF/> : </S>
</P>
