<P>
<S ID='S-44' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> The temporal relation between these continuations and the portion of earlier text they attach to is constrained along the lines sketched before . </S>
<S ID='S-45' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> The problem here is determining which thread in <CREF/> they continue ; <CREF/> continues the thread in which Sam rings the bell , but <CREF/> continues the thread in which Sam loses the key . </S>
</P>
<P>
<S ID='S-46' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> A further ambiguity is that when the third sentence is past perfect , it may be a continuation of a preceding thread or the start of a new thread itself . </S>
<S ID='S-47' IA='OWN' AZ='OWN'> Consider : </S>
</P>
